HEADWORD: Laudatory
<hw>Laud"a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>laudatorius</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>laudatoire</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining praise, or to the expression of praise; <as>as,
<ex>laudatory</ex> verses; the <ex>laudatory</ex> powers of
Dryden.</as></def> <rj><au>Sir J. Stephen.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
